tieth-century psychoanalytic and sociological texts arguing for a contemporary approach to the phenomenon of voluntary death, seeking to learn from such conceptual repertoires, as well as to acknowledge their limits. Leaving concludes on the anthropological question of how to account for the ethics of assistance with suicide: to grasp the actuality and composition of the ethical work that goes on in the configuration of a subject, one who is making a judgment about dying, with other participants and observers, the anthropologist included.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mai 2021) 0aAssisted suicidezSwitzerlandy21st century. 0aSuicide victimsvCase studies. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / General.2bisacsh  aanthropology.  aassisted suicide.  acasuistry.  adeath with dignity.  adeath.  adoctors.  aethics.  aeuthanasia.  aexit.  agrief.  ahealthcare.  ahuman life.  ajesuit moral theology.  amax weber.  amedical ethics.  amedicine.  amorality.  anonfiction.  aphysician assisted suicide.  aquality of life.  aright to die.  asocial science.  asuicide.  aswiss academy of medical sciences.  aswiss medical association.  aswitzerland.  aterminal illness.  avoluntary assisted dying.  avoluntary death.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDTL Humanities 2020z978311073776908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Social Sciences 2020 Englishz978311070472308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology, Education, Psychology 2020z9783110704549oZDB-23-SEW08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press Front